<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1064506>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Raricirrus jennae sp. nov. A, Holotype (USNM 1437642) in dorsal view; B, paratype (USNM 1437643) anterior end, lateral view; C, parapodium 8, left side; D, parapodium 21, left side; E, neuropodial spine and notopodial spine from chaetiger 8; F, neuropodial spine and notopodial spine from chaetiger 21; G, posterior end of holotype, ventral view; H, posterior segments with pygidium, dorsal view; I, anterior end in dorsal view showing heart body; J, individual with anterior end regenerating. (abbreviations: an, anus; hb, heart body; mo, mouth; mvr, mid-ventral ridge; nuO, nuchal organ; pr, prostomium;per, peristomium; py, pygidium)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1064506/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

